title: Bug 110566: Wrong data set result returned when setting an invalid filter expression for row[0]
description: When setting a filter expression like 'row[0] equals to 0' or when returning null result set.
OB: When setting an invalid filter expression for row[0], the data set returns incorrect results.
EB: The data set should not return any results when an invalid filter expression is set for row[0]. An error message indicating an invalid filter expression should be displayed.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Set a filter in the data set with the expression 'row[0] equals to '
2. Click on the Preview tab.
